solution: ```class Solution {
public:
    int nextBeautifulNumber(int n) {
        auto isBalanced = [](int x) -> bool {
            int cnt[10] = {};
            while (x) {
                int d = x % 10;
                if (d == 0) return false;
                cnt[d]++;
                x /= 10;
            }
            for (int d = 1; d <= 9; ++d)
                if (cnt[d] && cnt[d] != d) return false;
            return true;
        };
        for (int x = n + 1; ; ++x)
            if (isBalanced(x)) return x;
    }
};
```
efficiency: HIGH
time complexity: O((ans - n) * log ans)
space complexity: O(1)
energy implications: LOW
explanation: Brute-force check every integer greater than n until the first balanced number is found. The digit-counting lambda runs in O(log x) time per candidate. Empirically, the gap to the next balanced number is small (≤ 1333 for n ≤ 10^6), so the loop terminates quickly.

